        <li><a href="../owners.html">Owners</a></li>
        <li>@org/team-a</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="meta">Team · 2 repositories</p>

    

    <div class="scorecard">
        
        <div class="card tier-warn">
            <p class="card-label">Security Policy</p>
            <p class="card-value">50.0% (1/2)</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill tier-warn w-50"></div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="card-detail"><a href="../OPERATIONS.html#security-policy-coverage" title="Security Policy remediation guidance">Read more</a></p>
            
        </div>
        
        <div class="card tier-pass">
            <p class="card-label" title="Do we scan for leaked secrets? Counts this owner's public repositories only, mirroring the organisation-wide Secret Scanning figure.">Secret Scanning</p>
            <p class="card-value">100.0% (1/1)</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill tier-pass w-100"></div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="card-detail"><a href="../OPERATIONS.html#secret-scanning-coverage" title="Secret Scanning remediation guidance">Read more</a></p>
            
        </div>
        
        <div class="card tier-warn">
            <p class="card-label">Dependabot Status</p>
            <p class="card-value">50.0% (1/2)</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill tier-warn w-50"></div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="card-detail"><a href="../OPERATIONS.html#dependabot-coverage" title="Dependabot Status remediation guidance">Read more</a></p>
            
        </div>
        
        <div class="card tier-warn">
            <p class="card-label">Branch Protection</p>
            <p class="card-value">50.0% (1/2)</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill tier-warn w-50"></div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="card-detail"><a href="../OPERATIONS.html#branch-protection-coverage" title="Branch Protection remediation guidance">Read more</a></p>
            
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <p class="card-label">Stale Repos <span class="tooltip-trigger" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Repos not updated in 2+ years, out of this owner&#39;s total. The complement (total - stale) / total is this owner&#39;s Freshness rate, one of six controls behind the Team Health score. Distinct from the org-wide Archival Coverage, which measures what fraction of already-stale repos have been archived." title="Repos not updated in 2+ years, out of this owner&#39;s total. The complement (total - stale) / total is this owner&#39;s Freshness rate, one of six controls behind the Team Health score. Distinct from the org-wide Archival Coverage, which measures what fraction of already-stale repos have been archived.">ⓘ</span></p>
            <p class="card-value">0 / 2</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill w-0"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    
    <h2>Repositories</h2>
    <div class="table-wrapper">
        <table class="data-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Repository name; links to it on GitHub when a URL is known." title="Repository name; links to it on GitHub when a URL is known.">Repository</span></th>
                    <th><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="The repository's GitHub visibility: Public, Internal, or Private." title="The repository's GitHub visibility: Public, Internal, or Private.">Visibility</span></th>
                    <th class="text-center"><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Arithmetic mean: 100 × passing / measured controls, across five controls — Security Policy, Secret Scanning, Dependabot, Branch Protection, CODEOWNERS. Unmeasured controls (unknown, permission-denied, or not-applicable) are excluded from the denominator. Unlike the owner-level Team Health score, this includes CODEOWNERS. N/A when none are scorable." title="Arithmetic mean: 100 × passing / measured controls, across five controls — Security Policy, Secret Scanning, Dependabot, Branch Protection, CODEOWNERS. Unmeasured controls (unknown, permission-denied, or not-applicable) are excluded from the denominator. Unlike the owner-level Team Health score, this includes CODEOWNERS. N/A when none are scorable.">Repo Posture</span></th>
                    
                    <th class="text-center"><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Security policy presence — a SECURITY.md file (repo root, .github/, or docs/) or GitHub&#39;s security-policy setting enabled. Same per-repo check behind both this column and the org-wide Security Policy Coverage metric (non-public repos excluded as not applicable)." title="Security policy presence — a SECURITY.md file (repo root, .github/, or docs/) or GitHub&#39;s security-policy setting enabled. Same per-repo check behind both this column and the org-wide Security Policy Coverage metric (non-public repos excluded as not applicable).">Security Policy</span></th>
                    
                    <th class="text-center"><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="GitHub secret scanning presence — catches leaked credentials pushed to the repo. Same per-repo check behind both this column and the org-wide Secret Scanning Coverage metric (that metric&#39;s rate counts public repos only; the check itself runs regardless of visibility)." title="GitHub secret scanning presence — catches leaked credentials pushed to the repo. Same per-repo check behind both this column and the org-wide Secret Scanning Coverage metric (that metric&#39;s rate counts public repos only; the check itself runs regardless of visibility).">Secret Scanning</span></th>
                    
                    <th class="text-center"><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Dependabot security updates presence — when enabled, GitHub opens automatic pull requests for vulnerable dependencies. Same per-repo check behind both this column and the org-wide Dependabot Status metric." title="Dependabot security updates presence — when enabled, GitHub opens automatic pull requests for vulnerable dependencies. Same per-repo check behind both this column and the org-wide Dependabot Status metric.">Dependabot Status</span></th>
                    
                    <th class="text-center"><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Branch protection at the T2 accept-bar or better — pull request review required, on top of T1&#39;s force-push and deletion blocking. Same per-repo check behind both this column and the org-wide Branch Protection metric." title="Branch protection at the T2 accept-bar or better — pull request review required, on top of T1&#39;s force-push and deletion blocking. Same per-repo check behind both this column and the org-wide Branch Protection metric.">Branch Protection</span></th>
                    
                    <th><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Repository description from GitHub, or — when none is set." title="Repository description from GitHub, or — when none is set.">Description</span></th>
                    <th><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Primary language GitHub detected for the repository, or — when none is set." title="Primary language GitHub detected for the repository, or — when none is set.">Language</span></th>
                    <th class="text-center"><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Yes if this repository is a fork of another repository." title="Yes if this repository is a fork of another repository.">Fork</span></th>
                    <th><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="SPDX license identifier detected for the repository, or — when none is set." title="SPDX license identifier detected for the repository, or — when none is set.">License</span></th>
                    <th><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Timestamp of the repository's most recent git push, from the GitHub API's repository record — distinct from Last Commit below, which is scoped to the default branch." title="Timestamp of the repository's most recent git push, from the GitHub API's repository record — distinct from Last Commit below, which is scoped to the default branch.">Last Push</span></th>
                    <th><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Timestamp of when the repository was created on GitHub." title="Timestamp of when the repository was created on GitHub.">Created</span></th>
                    <th><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="GitHub login of the author of the most recent commit on the default branch; links to their profile when known." title="GitHub login of the author of the most recent commit on the default branch; links to their profile when known.">Last Committer</span></th>
                    <th><span class="tooltip-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Date of the most recent commit on the repository's default branch." title="Date of the most recent commit on the repository's default branch.">Last Commit</span></th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
